      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now officially within their relationship, Falke finds something inescapable about herself holding her back from what her heart yearns for.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;(This is a sequel to The Dreamers Wake.)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1332653-but-my-mind-holds-the-key/chapter/1332655/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;God Lives&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Falke sat on the couch with a novel, trying to keep her eyes on the unfolding storyline before her and not have them wandering off to the bedroom door just around the corner. She couldn’t hear them, not all the time, but she could feel them constantly, could almost picture the sweet-talking, kissing, biting, and thrusting in her head. She lowered her eyes to the book and turned a page, but a sudden jolt rippled through her torso and arms, making her shake the book, and what followed after was the quiet, but unmistakable growl of a low-pitched moan. Whether it had come from Elster or Ariane, she couldn’t tell, but Falke had felt it before she had heard it. She sighed- this had been going on for over an hour and a half.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She closed her book with a grumble and looked around the living room she sat in: the rows of books and movies on shelves were absent, save for a couple sitting by themselves next to the television; the paintings which once sat on the walls were removed and all sat in a stack on the side of the room with many towers of cardboard boxes accompanying them. Elster had finally managed to find a bigger apartment for the three while they still tried for more, and thanks to a little behind-the-scenes ‘encouragement’ from Falke, the apartment supervisor offered it to them at an extremely competitive rate. She knew Elster and Ariane tried to avoid altering their new reality as much as possible, to maintain a feeling of realness and not blind fantasy, but Falke was always willing to bend the rules a little just for them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Because they deserved it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They would be moving at the end of the season, but until then, it was business as usual, and for Elster and Ariane, there was a lot of business to be had.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke felt another reverberation coming from the bedroom and tensed up just as the whisper reached her ears.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A plentiful amount of business, indeed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane joked to her while Elster was out of earshot that they wanted to ‘make the most of the mattress’ before they left for their new place, but so far it seemed as though they were just excited about moving to an apartment where they would have room for their eventual family, and that excitement led to other forms of excitement.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And Falke was excited too, even as she tried to hide and bottle it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster and Ariane had noticed. They had invited her to join them on more than one occasion, and she already regularly slept through the night with them both, but joining them in that way-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t feel she was ready.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But she wanted to be.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke closed her eyes and breathed deeply in and out. Replika were not programmed to feel these kinds of physical desires, let alone feelings like love and yearning, and she was woefully under-equipped to deal with them herself. But damn it if she didn’t try.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her forehead crystals softly glowed as she constructed a space for her to feel the things she wanted so badly. A Gestalt body modeled after her biosynthetic one: commandingly tall, thin, lithe, limbs graceful as a dancer’s. She laid her simulacra atop a pillowy bed and tried to pleasure herself. She rubbed up and down every part of her that ached for touch, ran her fingers up and down a body that begged for intimacy, and even found herself with her hands clenched around her neck, fighting for control over a body that she created but was not hers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t enough; all she could do was wish they were another’s hands.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Still, it was a good start, but as she tried to bring Elster and Ariane into her space to complete her desire she kept messing up details about them. Their faces were blank, hands too small or too large, and bodies sometimes twisted or deformed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They weren’t real like the women in the room just next to her, and no matter how hard she tried, her mind rejected her built fantasy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke opened her eyes to the sound of a door opening, but only stared blankly at the now blank television across from her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Falke, are you alright?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster’s voice finally reached her and she blinked rapidly. “I am fine, yes, yes,” she said, having to turn her head in multiple directions before she found which angle Elster looked at her from. Her hair was very frazzled and messy, and her eyes a bit dulled from exhaustion, but what immediately jumped out the most to Falke was that she only wore a pair of loose pyjama bottoms. This left her completely topless, presenting a veritable cornucopia of a body that begged for her attention; she fought against the urge to not be seen staring at her well-defined rows of abdominal muscles glistening with a light sheen of sweat, her thick, corded arms as she stretched her equally fierce shoulders, or her round, full, endlessly squeezable breasts, adorned with her perky, firm nipples.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke was born with the essence of godhood instilled in her, an attitude that was only encouraged and enforced by the dozens of controllers and Protektors who served directly under her, but to Falke, the very fact that a perfectly chiselled being in both mind and body such as Elster before her wasn’t being actively worshipped felt profane to her, and she begged herself to be allowed to be the one to do so.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster scratched the back of her head and frowned as she fought back a yawn. “I had to call out to you three times before you answered. Are you sure you’re okay?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke quickly put a hand up to her lips as she feigned a light cough, but it still took her a while to answer Elster again, she was too preoccupied by new sounds coming from the bathroom next to the bedroom: a running faucet, and someone who could only be Ariane gargling water, followed by a heavy spit. She did this thrice before she finally exited the bathroom for the bedroom again, during which Falke took in a slow breath and exhaled quickly, trying to compartmentalize and push aside the mental image screaming into her head from the knowledge of what Ariane must have been doing in bed with Elster. However, as Ariane left the bathroom, she briefly saw Falke and Elster in the living room and silently waved at them, meaning Falke also saw her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane’s hair was also a mess, showing frazzles in every direction, but her eyes and smile carried an energy of yearning for more, made even more apparent when she blew Elster a playful kiss. But yet again, what caught Falke’s attention the most was what Ariane was wearing, or rather, what she wasn’t. She had on only her semi-transparent nightgown, which months ago would not have even batted an eye, but it was a small piece of lingerie meant for a small body, and wonderful, peaceful domesticity had certainly caught up to the snow-haired woman. It certainly helped that her new partner Falke was more than willing to cook for her and Elster any amount and frequency of gourmet meals she was born with the knowledge of.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke only saw Ariane for a couple of seconds before she dipped back into the bedroom, but that was enough to see that the hem of the nightgown which had once gone comfortably below her buttocks now sat almost right in the centre line of her hips, and there was more to discover as she turned to blow her kiss to Elster. Falke almost gasped as she saw Ariane’s nightgown now didn’t even fully cover her still visibly moist and bare folds, and the front of the garment, slick with sweat, stuck to her body in such a way that it didn’t not hide any of her newly developing luscious curves, including the small, but growing pouch of her tummy which all knew would only grow even more should their efforts in the bedroom succeed. She had seen it lightly spilled over the waistband of jeans and shorts before, but seeing the full picture alongside the visible outline of her also widening navel and the sheer radiance of Ariane’s being once again compelled Falke’s blasphemous urge to worship.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke struggled to not sigh. They were both perfect in every way. So much more perfect than her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She coughed again once Ariane had left and she had pulled her mind out of its spiral of desire and self-doubt. “It’s alright,” she assured Elster. “Just had my mind pre-occupied,” she half-lied.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded and went to sit down on the spot next to her on the couch. Just her hip brushing up against hers sent lightning bolts through her body, but then Elster put her hand atop her knee, and she had to fight not to shudder greatly against this innocent contact.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster blinked strongly before she sighed, fidgeting her legs as she sat. “Well… well… um…” She paused to exhale slowly. “Are you ready for bed? Ari isn’t very tired, but I could probably…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re not finished?” Falke croaked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster didn’t answer verbally, but bit her lip and slowly raised her hands and shoulders into a hesitant shrug.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “Take your time,” she said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster also nodded and slowly stood up, but soon after she started walking back to the bedroom she spun around and looked almost pleadingly at Falke.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you think-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you, but… not yet,” Falke finished for her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster sighed and gave her a thumbs-up before she rounded the corner. A moment later she heard the door click shut again, and she picked up her book.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She got the same amount of reading done through this session as well: a singular, rather short page.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane came out around twenty minutes later to find Falke staring at the blank television once again, only this time, she was alert enough to notice when she had entered the living room and turned and smiled at her once she came fully into view. Internally, Falke breathed a silent sigh of relief that Ariane had swapped her sweat-slicked nightgown for one of Elster’s larger t-shirts, the long, opaque garment thankfully reaching low enough to cover everything her increasingly too-small nightgown failed to.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“We’re uh, heading to bed now,” Ariane informed her, letting out a short yawn after she finished.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The question wasn’t asked, but statements like this one implied it: did Falke want to sleep with them tonight? She was comfortable enough to do so on occasion, usually taking up the outer side of any cuddle pile they organized and forming a basket with her long arms and legs to wrap around both Elster and Ariane.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke looked down for a moment. She wasn’t sure if being near the two wives would be such a good idea while she was still burdened by desire, but as she briefly glanced back up at Ariane’s eyes and saw the optimistic glow in her eyes, she felt like she had to say yes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;So, she nodded and stood up, and Ariane gave a short hop of excitement before pressing her palms together; Falke almost felt her systems seize up for a brief moment as Ariane’s impromptu hop sparked a noticeable ripple up her thighs, tummy, and finally chest, still visible even through the loose shirt which mostly hung off her shoulders.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke, you coming?” Ariane asked, snapping her out of her uncontrollable thoughts.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She blinked and caught back up to Ariane, who smiled once they were side-by-side. Then, on pure instinct, Falke brought her arms up just as Ariane leaped into them, her reflexes knowing what she would do even before she did. Ariane nuzzled against Falke’s shoulder as she carried her into the bedroom, yawning once again as she carefully laid her down atop the mattress. On the far side was Elster, splayed out on her back fast asleep with the covers only partially across her legs; Falke tried not to stare at her exposed upper body and restart her spiraling, only watching Ariane as she carefully moved Elster’s arm to her side before she wiggled into place in the middle of the bed, leaving a space to her other side just for her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Once she was in, Ariane wasted no time in playing little spoon to Falke’s big spoon, and she sighed peacefully as she settled into place and Falke pulled the covers up the three with her bioresonance. As she wrapped her arms around Ariane, skipping Elster for now to avoid waking her up, Ariane brought her hand to her lips and kissed the backs of her fingers, sending a light shockwave of sensation up her arm and throughout her body with every touch.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can you believe we have all of this?” Ariane whispered. “I still have trouble believing it from time to time.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke held Ariane a little more snugly. “Truthfully, I have a hard time remembering many details of my past life… it is as if I started here, with you both,” she whispered back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane turned her head slightly to the side, managing to get a peek at Falke’s face from the corner of her eye. “Because of the whole issue of having our memories?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“No, at least, not entirely,” Falke answered, pausing to kiss the top of Ariane’s head. “It is more… I was not an individual before this. I was… a symbol, a divine one, indeed, but still ultimately a symbol. I was given a role to play, and I played it… so many seasons of nothing but administrative monotony, never being allowed to form connections, to seek out life and change, or stray from my path in any way. I was a god, but I was just as confined and trapped as every other Replika and Gestalt at the facility… but now I am free. I am liberated to be whoever I want to be. It is the start of a life, or at the very least, a new one.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But…” Ariane returned her head forward and sank back into Falke’s body. “Have you not just traded one aspect of desire for another? Our desires?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke found Ariane’s hand and held it firmly. “I chose to be here with you both, and you chose to have me as part of your lives. That is all that matters to me.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane took a short breath and exhaled softly. “Okay… thank you…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward, Elster snorted in her sleep, and her two partners realized jointly that it would be best to keep conversation to a minimum, lest they wake her up. Ariane brought Falke’s hand to her lips again and began to gently kiss each of the digits on her hand before moving to do the same to each of her knuckles.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m glad you chose to come here and be with us,” Ariane as quietly as possible whispered before she kissed the palm of Falke’s hand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled under Ariane’s kisses, but the longer she went on, the more curious her displays of affection grew. She started bringing her knuckles past her lips to suck on, followed by her finger tips. She reached for Falke’s thigh behind her and rubbed her hands up and down the smooth polyethylene shell, even giving her a light squeeze once. Then, she noticed Ariane start to wiggle her hips and legs together, sighing wistfully as she let go of her hand, and through it all, Falke felt more and more tense until she finally heard the telltale sounds of rhythmic, peaceful sleeping that signaled she was finally asleep.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke finally began to relax and nod off as well, shutting down her primary systems to enter sleep mode, but right in the middle of falling asleep she felt Ariane squirm ever so gently again and snapped back fully awake. She looked over Ariane’s cheek and saw she was still asleep, but also that she still continued to wiggle and pant.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…” Ariane quietly muttered, moaning softly afterward. “Touch…” she added before sighing heavily and relaxing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane quieted down and returned to sleep, but Falke only stared at the ceiling.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t get any more sleep that night.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster was the first to wake up in the morning, though, with Falke never having truly fallen asleep, it might have been more accurate to say she was the second. She blinked her eyes open and almost immediately saw Falke to her left lying on her back, eyes open and unblinking toward the ceiling. She tried to lean forward but came to the realization that Ariane had shifted in her sleep, and had a significant portion of her body resting atop her, with her head planted almost face down into her chest.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…?” she whispered. The Replika rolled over onto her shoulder and got a good view of the situation, smiling lightly at the picture of Ariane softly sleeping and snoring into Elster’s cleavage. “Mind giving me a hand?” Elster whispered, pointing at the sleeping beauty atop her. Falke nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her forehead crystals started to glow softly as she gently cupped the back of Ariane’s head with her hand and began to carefully roll Ariane onto her back using bioresonance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ellie… come back…” Ariane mumbled in her sleep as she came to a rest on her back, followed by more quiet, sleepy breathing. Elster cupped her mouth and tried not to giggle too loudly at her wife’s subconscious thoughts, but Falke bit her lip hard as she saw what Ariane was doing with her hand under the covers as she slept. She tugged the covers up past Ariane’s stomach to try and give her a modicum of privacy, but in doing so she only made Elster curious, and soon she leaned her head over to watch what her wife’s fidgeting arm was doing; she quickly snapped back and pressed her hand against her mouth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward a minute of quiet, awkward silence only punctuated by Ariane briefly snorting and groaning in her sleep, Falke deftly slipped out of bed and gave herself a light stretch; a mostly unnecessary thing to do for a Replika, but also a quirk of Gestalt neural imprinting that still felt right to do.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I will go prepare breakfast,” Falke quietly stated. Elster gave her a thumbs up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll stay here for… a bit… if that’s alright,” Elster answered, briefly looking down at the still-sleeping Ariane. Falke nodded and left the room, breathing a sigh of relief as the door clicked shut behind her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She briskly walked into the kitchen, hoping that absorbing herself in cooking would take her mind off things. Her bioresonance crystals shone brightly as she assembled her tools and ingredients: She grabbed a large metal bowl and whisk with her hands as the fridge opened and a carton of milk and a few eggs floated to her workstation, followed shortly after by tubs of sugar, flour, and salt, and finally a container of cooking oil. She carefully weighed all of her measurements on a kitchen scale before adding them one at a time to the bowl, finishing by tapping the eggs on the countertop and cracking them into the bowl. Falke wetted a cloth and wrung it out so it was just damp, wrapping it around the base of her metal bowl to keep it still as she furiously beat the mixture with a whisk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She smiled; Ariane and Elster had an electric whisk she could have used, she had gotten it for them, but after a while in the relationship she developed a taste for preparing as much as she could by hand, especially for them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It felt better.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With her batter fully whisked and completely smooth, Falke put the bowl in the fridge to rest while she prepared the other components of the meal. Into a small saucepan on medium heat went the contents of a can of sliced strawberries, juice included, slowly adding in sugar and a small amount of salt as it heated up and softly bubbled. She would have greatly preferred to prepare the compote using fresh fruit, but she had made a promise to her partners to avoid pilfering ingredients, and fresh fruit was one commodity that was prohibitively expensive in a world like Rotfront which was still undergoing the process of klimaforming.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She finished the mixture with just the right amount of ground cinnamon, ginger, and lemon juice to complement and enhance the sweet, jammy compote. Again, she would have preferred to use fresh lemon zest to finish the compote, but bottled lemon juice would have to do.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With the strawberry compote finished, she twisted the burner’s knob to low heat to keep it warm while she shifted her focus to preparing drinks. Ariane had lost her taste for coffee recently, complaining that no matter what it always tasted too bitter, so she went about preparing a milk tea mixture, boiling some bags of black tea while she prepared a mixture of half-and-half and sweetened condensed milk. Once the tea was steeped, she stuck it in the freezer for a minute to cool to room temperature while she retrieved a pre-made mixture of tapioca pearls in brown sugar syrup, adding some of it to a tall glass alongside the milk mixture and tea once it was sufficiently chilled, and finishing the glass off with a wide straw to accompany the tapioca pearls.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward, it was a relatively simpler affair of preparing Elster’s latte and her own doppio; again, she ground the beans and steamed the milk using hand tools rather than the fancy espresso machine she had acquired for them, and she didn’t hesitate to draw a little latte art of a butterfly on the top of Elster’s drink.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The only thing left was to prepare the crepes. Once her crepe pan had fully pre-heated she ladled the perfect amount on, smiling as the chilled and rested mixture smoothly spread to the edges of the pan just by tilting and rotating it. She topped three plates with their own wide, thin crepe, spooned a generous helping of strawberry compote atop each, and finished her creations with a ring of whipped cream and dusted chocolate powder for maximum flourish.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She set up each of their dishes and drinks at the dinner table and let out a satisfied sigh as she absorbed the picture before her in her head. All that was left was to wait for the other two lovebirds to emerge hungry and well-rested from their bedroom.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But they did not emerge after she knocked on the door and announced that breakfast was ready.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a few minutes of increasingly tense waiting she leaned her ear up to the door.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And immediately regretted it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She walked back to the living room and sat on the couch, staring at her own anxious reflection in the dark screen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a minute of staring and tapping her hoof on the carpet below her, she finally spoke up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Just go in there,” she said to herself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You haven’t been invited,” her reflection answered.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I don’t need an invitation, they want me there with them.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Then why didn’t they ask you?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“They’re polite.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“They’re different.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“They care, they understand.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re different.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke took a moment to look down at her cold, titanium hands before she squeezed them shut. “It doesn’t matter to them.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her reflection laughed. “It matters to you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke clenched her eyes shut and took in a sharp breath. She briefly wondered how AEON command would feel if one of their prized Falke units, the Nation’s wunderwaffe found itself on the verge of tears, to say nothing else of the intractable number of grave sins she was guilty of simply by being in this relationship.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re pathetic.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She covered her face with her hands. “Be quiet,” she weakly cried.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Want to prove us wrong? Go open their door.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a moment to hear her voice echo in her own head, a sense of defiance overtook Falke. She did not raise to her hooves, instead, she floated herself up from the couch and straight to Ariane and Elster’s bedroom door, gently landing on the floor just as she grasped the doorknob with her hand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She shook; her hand shook.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a moment of tensing up her synthetic muscles, Falke sighed dejectedly as she let go of the doorknob.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“See? Pathetic.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She was just about to turn away and head back into the kitchen when an unexpected sound froze Falke in her tracks.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The door opened behind her, and a moment later a soft, caring, and loving voice spoke out to her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…? Is everything okay?” Ariane asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She turned around with streaks of optical lubricant fluid running down from her eyes. “No,” she croaked, but then quickly swallowed and added more clearly. “Breakfast is ready, by the way.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane nodded and stepped out of the doorway, still in nothing but Falke’s t-shirt, only now, Falke looked at nothing but her eyes. Elster followed her wife shortly after, now with a loose, white t-shirt over her top, and Falke instinctively dropped to her knees.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They both hugged her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you want to talk about it?” Ariane whispered to her after their hug ended. Falke shook her head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll be okay,” she assured them both. “This is… still a lot for me.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey, I get it,” Elster said, giving Falke’s shoulder a light squeeze before she got back up on her hooves. “I really do,” she repeated.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. She knew Elster was telling the truth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Come, while your meals are still warm,” Falke spoke out, forcing a smile on their lips.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And so, she showed them to their meals.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster wasted no time in digging into her crepe. She furiously hacked off pieces with her knife and fork to shovel into her mouth, not caring that her wild eating habits were getting bits of compote syrup and whipped cream all over her cheeks and nose. Meanwhile, Ariane took a more restrained approach. She took a moment to appreciate the sweet aromas coming from her plate before she cut off a small piece of crepe, ensuring that there was some strawberry and whipped cream on it before she forked it into her mouth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane immediately started smiling as she chewed. “How did you get to be such an amazing chef, Falke?” she asked after swallowing her first bite.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded as she looked back at Ariane’s crimson eyes, also noticing out of the corner of her vision that Elster also looked at her as she continued to wolf away at her meal. She took her first bite and swallowed it, putting down her knife and fork before she answered the question.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke units are not intended to be just military commanders, but also as diplomatic envoys,” she explained, watching Ariane nod along as she took a quick pause to sip her espresso. “Some extremely high-ranking party officials are also provided a Falke unit to serve as a personal adjutant. For these reasons, we were additionally programmed with a high degree of culinary, etiquette, rhetorical, and linguistic expertise.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I see,” Ariane acknowledged. “And did you make use of these skills before now?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “I… cooked meals for myself and… others, on occasion.” She took another sip of her espresso and smiled. “I enjoy cooking, it is… relaxing, soothing. It is something I have full control over.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I can definitely understand that,” Ariane said. She brought her glass of milk tea forward to take a sip, with some of the pearls shooting up the wide straw.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster suddenly began to choke loudly, and both Ariane and Falke turned to face her the moment she started trying to cough. Falke wasted no time; she rose from her chair and got behind Elster, pulling her up from her seat and thrusting up her abdomen with her fist, she soon spat out a nearly intact slice of strawberry, gasping for air as Falke gently lowered her back down.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh my god, Ellie, are you okay?” Ariane asked, leaning over the table to get a better view of her partner.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster gave her a weak thumbs-up with one hand while she kept the other on her throat, gently rubbing as she tried to calm down her breathing. “I’m fine,” she eventually coughed out. “Just… gotta learn to chew,” she joked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane laughed alongside her, but Falke looked away, unable to join in the teasing. She had seen where Elster was looking right before she started choking: Ariane’s drink, and in particular, the straw she used to suck up the milk tea with pearls. She also caught a glimpse of what it had made Elster’s heart want.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What she also wanted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The rest of breakfast finished smoothly, if rather quietly, and Elster soon returned to her room to get changed for the day.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Shouldn’t you shower?” Falke heard Ariane ask as she scrubbed the dishes clean.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Gah, no time, don’t want to be late.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Alright, I’ll come help you get ready.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“A-Actually, Ari, I think I should get changed alone.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There was a brief pause. Falke’s hand shook just as Ariane’s whispered words reached her ear.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Come on, I’ll be quick, I promise.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The bedroom door clicked shut soon after, and Falke gasped as she stopped holding her breath. She tried to focus on cleaning all of the plates, pans, and cutlery she used in making her meal, but as she dredged her scrub brush in the hot, soapy water, she was reminded of an inescapable fact.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her hands didn’t feel the heat of the water.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They were mechanical hands, an artificial creation like the rest of her, nothing but metal and clockwork. Even if some parts of her body could be called organic, and she possessed most of the senses of a Gestalt, and looked like one at a glance, there was no escaping that she was not human.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But they were.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She laid the plate in her hand back in the sink and gripped the countertop, sighing softly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t want to consider it, but a new thought wouldn’t leave her mind.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Maybe she had made a mistake.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
