      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Layla unwittingly discovers an alien scout on her apartment's roof during her Friday night smoke session.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1327809-synaptic-eclipse/chapter/1327813/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;1 &amp;#8211; Layla&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Fridays are for letting loose. That's my mantra as I lay on the couch. Brew on the side table (a repurposed moving box), anime reruns I've already seen playing at my desk. My thoughts jumble as the weed sinks in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Tired from work, no one to talk to, drugs are my temporary escape. The second shift premium hardly keeps me running week to week. Thankfully weed is legal here, cheap too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Letting my high control my mood, I drift by the difficult and the painful. Avoiding harsher thoughts, I try to let myself mellow out. Looking out my window at the night sky, stars dulled by the city lights, the waning moon still shining, somehow. My mind can't help but dance at the surface of the dark side.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;My job sucks, don't wanna think about that. Pay could be better too, at least I've got this apartment. Friends all moved for work or are on different shifts, hardly any company these days. No need to dwell on that now, I've already spent too much time down and ruminating about it. Looking at my desk, I eye the stylus. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Maybe art can get me out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;, I think, more pessimistic than not.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;I get up and draw for a bit. Dumb little doodles. Idly drawing the moon in negative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;I wonder if I'm stuck. No way out, trapped in an eternal loop of jobs that I can stand just a bit more than the last. Maybe I'll miss some steps and have to try hard for improvement. Maybe there's a ceiling? I don't know. I banish the subject.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;It's Friday after all, late at night. I let loose like I should. Like I need. I zone out. Turn the anime down. Doom scroll for a bit and then shitpost in servers full of friends I don't get to see anymore. Take a bleary nap and then masturbate to the thought of affection. A couple hours pass.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Taking advantage of a spark of productivity, I start to tidy my apartment back up. Some dishes get put in the dishwasher. Put some errant trash in the bin. I pour out my bong water and rinse out my piece. Satisfied with my work, I get a tinge of disappointment as I feel myself starting to come down.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Fridays are for letting loose, right?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt; I think to myself, eyeing the clock on the microwave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;1AM, it screams into my irises. I figure that I probably shouldn't smoke anymore tonight, then I wipe the moisture out of my bowl, and pack another. Not wanting to miss my fade into nothingness when I go to bed, I pop an edible. Grabbing a warm hoodie, my lighter and my keys, I lock my door behind me as I head upstairs. Popping in one earbud and scrolling for something to listen to, I walk up the stairs from my top floor apartment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Watching a bunch of YouTube locksmithing videos had its benefits. A simple whim and an improvised rake got me on the roof of my building in the first few weeks here. My late schedule stops anyone from ever noticing me up there, so I hid a camping chair to use, and I usually go up to vibe to music, smoke, or both. While I'm allowed to smoke inside, I don't want visitors to deal with a bad smell and think I'm gross. (I'd have to actually have visitors first, though.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;With one hand I grab the little jumble of bent paper clips hanging on my key ring and shove them in the door. A bit of motion on the pins and the lock turns, letting me onto the roof. The door slams behind me while I make my decision and select an album. Holding my bong and digging for my light, I hear something strange. Almost like someone quickly shuffling a bunch of poker chips across the roof. More metallic?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Looking up, I see the strangest thing that I have ever seen in real life. At first, I’m pretty sure I’m seeing a big octopus. A bulbous ‘head’ seems to stare back, but it has too many limbs. There seem to be dozens, from long white strings to gray gripping appendages with soft orange lines running down them. Many are almost like jellyfish tendrils, a few more like squid or octopus limbs. Already alert, it raises itself higher, 4 feet or so tall, like it's an animal trying to intimidate me. It stands amongst a pile of strange little metal pieces that click and climb up its body. I watch as it's covered in strange semi-reflective segments, almost making it look like a big horrible crab or something. Cephalopod eyes dot its head at regular intervals. The ones facing in my direction stare right back at me as I watch it move slightly forward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;For a few moments, we simply lock eyes and wonder what the other will do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;I mutter to myself, “I'm not high enough for this to be a hallucination.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Wayward Two-Seventeen is getting tired, two remain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt; Simple report. Send it back to the field commander. A bit later, the transponder pings. Checking the response is a formality, the content is known and expected. Two more objects and today's calibration is over. Looking at the next object from above a window, this one sighs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;The automatic survey systems were pretty good, after calibration. Without that calibration, the system can have some trouble with objects of similar function but differing surface forms. This one scrolls through the generated diagrams for the strange object. Were the computer a bit better at large topologies, the risk of direct confirmation wouldn’t have been necessary, as it’s directly on top of a family home in a populous area. Still, one categorizes it: another signal receiver, as weird as it looks. A jumble of parallel and perpendicular metal tines, presumably to catch as much signal as possible, or something (one is not a comm systems expert). A simple selection and the computer system makes the connection. On to the next.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;The next location would be a minute or so away if the skyhook were authorized. Unfortunately it can't be authorized in middle density areas until the local survey is complete. This one takes a bit to directly navigate through the city. Even with active camouflage there’s some difficulty getting around without notice. The combination of the night cycle, and psyche of the population seems to work favorably here, despite all the lights.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Several minutes later, and one reaches the destination, a small nature preserve, of sorts. The towering local plants provide some cover from the sky and the lights of the city. There is, however, a light on a post, next to a piece of furniture. Across from them, a pretty simple object, unsurprising that it was saved for later in the survey. Running a finger over it, this one ponders the meaning of yet-untranslated symbols. A sign, of sorts? There were many symbols, as well as some detailed images of the nearby plants. Looking through the classifications, this one chooses. Analog information panel, low tech, but reliable for what seems to be a ‘low tech zone’ in this city. This one idly ponders the meaning of the symbols and leans against the rough spine of one of the big plants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Almost a turn later, and this one gets its extraction point. It'll be an hour or two while the skyhook positions, but the job is almost over. No more obligations other than getting out unnoticed. The system will do more detailed analysis. This one can relax until more input is needed. Compatibility testing is expected to start fairly soon, but there's no rush. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;One heads to the building designated as the extraction point. The maneuvering gear helps greatly with the climb up the side onto its roof. A relatively low-built area, away from the central city, the tallest structures are a group of residential buildings. the taller the location, the less chance of error during skyhook extraction. A quick security check once we reach the top - the access point is locked. The survey implies these roofs are for maintenance. Usually only accessed during the day. Analysis seems sound. One random out of place object, but both the system analysis and this one agree - it's no concern. The dominant species seems to produce unnecessary amounts of disposable or otherwise unimportant items. There's random stuff scattered everywhere on this planet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Secured area, plenty of time. This one petitions for rest permissions in the interim minutes. Permission granted. The tool rig is put on passive mode and set upon the floor. Relaxing a bit, this one studies the local moon. Bigger, closer, brighter. Nothing like the three at home. Its craters are easy to view from the surface, one considers the battering it must have taken over millennia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;One wonders what reaction the moon draws from the locals. The dominant species, as well as a few less developed creatures, were marked as high priority. “Human”, their most common designation for themselves. The humans were of particular interest, as their nervous systems (as well as that of most larger animals) were almost certainly link compatible. The first issue with attempting contact, though, is their current lack of unity. Despite their incredibly quick technological developments in the period since their initial discovery, their society is still not very peaceful or stable. The biggest issue comes after- many humans are estimated to be dangerous to interact with. Particularly, given the extreme anatomical differences, humans may not find one’s species, the Corda, a comforting existence. Those issues were made into one's own problem with this assignment. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;The issues aren’t that bothersome, the job will be done, and despite the time involved, one should be approved for research after. That was the agreement. This one would rather suffer in pursuit of its curiosity than fail to explore its fascination. Some turns pass, as one feels itself a bit relieved, ready for the somewhat unpleasant ride on the hook. Relaxed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Relaxed enough, that one's reaction to the door opening is far too slow. Clicks, and a creaking sound ring across the roof.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Perking up, feeling adrenaline release in the cortex. Panic. The human does not even look up from its data pad as the door slams shut loudly behind it. It begins to put the pad away and shuffle for something else, noticing nothing. Standing tall, some strange water filled object held aloft, it would only be a moment before one was noticed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;A finger on a switch and one's tool rig is set to active. It starts to reequip itself and, noticing the noise, the human looks up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;A long moment of extreme tension. Eyes lock. This shouldn't be happening. A terse message hastily sent to FC.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Compromised by civilian individual, reason for presence unknown, please advise.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;“...I'm not high enough for this to be a hallucination”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;It speaks, its meaning unknown. Pulling its limb out of its garment, it holds something. A quick motion and the rig runs an emergency scan. The human stops, speaking again,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;“Woah, hi! Sorry.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;One sends the same message to FC, appended with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;PLEASE ADVISE. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;The human turns its limbs slowly, holding its possessions aloft. Scan info returns before they're even halfway up, fed straight from a sensory link. They don't have any weapons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;FC responds, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;EVALUATING, RISKY INFO LINK ESTABLISHED, REMAIN PEACEFUL, APPREHEND IF NECESSARY, STAY SAFE.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;FC's concern for safety is both supportive and incredibly concerning. It's not in their standard parameters. The info link was expected and hoped for, FC has something near an hour of faster communication and a direct info feed from the tool rig. Situation depending, the feed should be cut after that time, before the comms burst becomes too easy to detect. The human takes a few slow steps back, lowering its body and placing the items on the ground. One realizes, it has held a finger up, pointed at the human, since initiating the scan. Perhaps too quickly, one's finger snaps back to a more neutral position. The human flinches at the sudden movement, then, it slowly raises its body back up, holding its open limbs up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;“Okayyy, I don't want to hurt you, can you, uh, understand me?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;More speech. Language models haven’t been developed yet, let alone speech replication. This one hopes FC won’t suggest the emergency contact protocol. The tool rig starts feeding anatomical data through the sensory link. One responds in frustration, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;CERTAINLY THERE IS A BETTER COURSE OF ACTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;FC’s message is too quick and too official to be a response to mine, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;W2-17, NEW OBJECTIVE: INITIATE EMERGENCY CONTACT PROTOCOL, HUMAN DESIGNATED ‘H1’ PENDING FURTHER INFORMATION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Incredible frustration gives way to resignation. Acceptance reigns, as one reengages closed pathways in its nervous system. The tool rig quietly and deliberately shifts away from this one’s claws. FC’s response to the outburst comes, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;UMBRAL CASCADE WAS SELECTED, IN PART, FOR STRONG PREVIOUS RECORD WITH FORCED CONTACT. H1 IS A NEAR IDEAL CANDIDATE FOR COVERT CONTACT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;A wince at the sore subject. Of course they’re a strong candidate, there’s no way they’d give that order if FC wasn’t certain. Flora like Field Command are grown to make these decisions, despite one's objections. One moves toward the human. Umbral Cascade stirs, ready to act.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
