      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;"You just haven't found the right one."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;That's what Jamie tells all the lesbians he met. He always wondered why lesbians existed in the first place. Sure, he understood the appeal of women and all. But he couldn't understand why women would be with other women. He's always been told that its not right. That's why he always asked them on dates. Maybe he'd be the one to change their minds.&lt;br /&gt; Most lesbians didn't give him the time of day though.&lt;br /&gt; Until one day, one of them said yes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1322953-you-just-havent-found-the-right-one/chapter/1322973/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/179226/greeneyedgal/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/44/ava_179226_1731686775.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/179226/greeneyedgal/"&gt;GreenEyedGal&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Finally posting my first long form series. This is actually me trying to rewrite a pretty rushed piece I made for a class that I was never fully satisfied with. My attempt really to flesh it out more. Hope y'all enjoy!&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Okay."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"What?" I wasn't sure I heard her right. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She flashed a smile, "I said, okay. Sure. Let's go on a date."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Okay, I &lt;em&gt;did&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;hear her right. "But why?" I managed to stammer out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her face turned harsher again, back to how it was when our conversation began.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Dude, you're the one who asked me out. And now you're the one wigging out on me?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Sorry..." Wait, why am I the one apologizing? "I just didn't expect you to say yes. No one's ever said yes before."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She smiled again at that. What's so funny? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"So, wait, I'm not the first one you asked out on a date who said yes?" She said, chuckling. "Sorry, but that sounds kind of pathetic, dude."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I could feel my face getting flush. This is so  embarrassing…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My roommate, Karl, 'thankfully', stepped up. "Uh, no? That's not what he meant." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Please, shut up... If I knew him at all, he's just going to make things worse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"He meant that you're the first lesbian he asked out who said yes."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"First what?" She glared at me&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Karl continued, "Yeah, he does this a lot. He asks lesbians he meets out on a date. And they always say no. You're the first one who said otherwise"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"That is SO wrong, dude," She looked really upset now. "What are you, some kind of lesbian chaser or something? Why don't you ask out straight girls instead of bothering us?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Well, maybe he IS a chaser, whatever that is? What's it to you, huh? And it's not his fault he doesn't ask out straight girls. He just says lesbians are more interesting. Isn't that right, bro?" &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I flinched at that. Karl looked straight to me. She followed suit. She was glaring daggers now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I had to shut Karl up &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;now&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Okay Karl, that is enough out of you." I pulled him away and pointed to our car. "Why don't you just bring our food to the car and we can just eat it at home. That sound good?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Okay, sure," he replied cheerily. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Before he left, I had to remind him though, "Oh yeah, before we forget again. Remember what I said about calling me 'bro'?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He smiled apologetically, "Oh shit, I forgot. I'm sorry about that, bro. I mean... Uh..."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Karl, it's okay. Just get the food in the car while it's still warm."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Will do." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And with that, he walked away, leaving me with her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"You two are an interesting pair." She spoke up, getting my full attention again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I looked back at Karl who’s sitting in the passenger seat, watching us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Yeah, he sure is something. Karl's a nice guy. Maybe not the best with words, especially when he's trying to defend someone. But he's always been good to me."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She smiled again. I'd take her smile over the piercing stare she was giving me earlier.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"So, what was that about you asking out lesbians all the time?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I got flustered again. Why did Karl have to dig me into this hole? He's great, but he really is like an excitable puppy or something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"I uh..."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"You said we were more interesting? Why'd you say that?" She was staring again. But she was still smiling. And I was definitely getting confused by her expression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"It's just..."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"You come on to me while I'm just trying to buy some food, you see my lesbian flag pin, and I don't even know how you know that's a lesbian flag, and you had the balls to tell me TO MY FACE that I'm probably just a lesbian because, and I quote, 'you just haven't found the right one'," she was getting really heated up. "And your friend there tells me that I'm not even the first lesbian you did this to?!"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"... Yes?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Okay."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"What?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"I said, okay. Dude, are your ears broken or something? Why do you always make me repeat myself?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I... I don't get her one bit. This girl is so confusing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"I thought you were mad."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Oh, I am," she said smiling. Why was she smiling? Is she really mad or? "Look, don't worry your pretty little head over it too much. Your forehead might get wrinkles, you know?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I instinctively put my hand on my forehead.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Ha. Cute," she snorted. "So, are we still on for our date?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"That's still happening?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She looked at me like I asked a dumb question.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Duh? Why wouldn't it still happen?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Weren't you... Offended or something?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She suddenly looked serious. "Hey, I admit, I only said yes the first time because I thought it was funny. But now I think it'd be good for you to have a date with me."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"What do you mean?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"I just think it would be good for you to actually hang out with a lesbian. Learn a thing or two maybe. Besides, better I nip it in the bud now before you go harass some other hapless sapphic.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"What?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"If you don't get it, don't worry about it. I was serious about the forehead wrinkles though. Those can sneak up on you."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Fine then.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Great!" She flashed a smile again. How could she smile at me so many times after all this? "So when do you want to have the date? Because I was kinda itching to go home and relax with my burger tonight."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I scratched the back of my neck, "I didn't really think I'd get this far. Never had anyone say yes so..."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She reached into her jacket pocket and took out her phone. "Okay here, gimme your number and I'll text you. That fine?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"That's good with me."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"What name should I put you down as?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"It's Jo–" I flinched. I knew I didn't like using it. But whenever someone asked me my name, I almost always instinctively say it. Got basically drilled into me by my dad. But... She doesn't know me. I can just say whatever name and it'll be alright, right? "It's Jamie."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Jamie, huh? Cute name."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I blushed at that. I don't know why but I could feel the telltale signs of my cheeks getting warmer. I instinctively covered my face a bit with my hands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"So... I guess, see you later then?" I said, trying to get away as soon as I can. I didn't think I could handle this conversation any longer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Yeah. See you later, dude." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I flinched again. "Please don't call me 'dude'", I muttered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She smiled at that. I don't know why. "Okay. Whatever you say, cutie."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I almost forgot, "Wait, what's your name?"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Sophia."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And with that, she left.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Princess Charming: he really said that?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: Yeah, couldn't believe it either. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perse: and you said yes?!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: well, he seemed interesting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perse: in what way?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: you'll see when you meet him. Might bring him around to our place if y'all are okay with it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perse: I mean, why not. Mostly just going to be me there with Cee out of town and all&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Princess Charming: Hey! It's not my fault I have friends other than you two.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: now now children, don't fight. You'll all get to meet him eventually. Just trust me, he's really interesting. Can't say anything for sure now. But something's pinging in me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perse: you mean?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: maybe. Who knows really. Either way, I think I can at least get him to learn a thing or two. Better for our community in general.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Princess Charming: praise be to you our lesbian savior&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: yes I am. Praise me more&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perse: so when's the first date?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;SophAmore: I'll keep you posted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
